snippet.title: AKG K551 headphones
snippet.description: The AKG K551s are closed portable headphones with an open, airy sound, but their relative lack of bass means they're actually better for use at home.

snippet.title: Apple's next act: Team up with Nike on a 'smartband'?
snippet.description: The company might not launch the long-awaited smartwatch, but could be partnering with Nike to deliver a new smartband that tracks activity -- according to a report.

snippet.title: How Target detected hack but failed to act -- Bloomberg
snippet.description: Despite alerts received through a $1.6 million malware detection system, Target failed to stop hackers from stealing credit card numbers and personal information of millions of customers, Bloomberg reports.

snippet.title: T-Mobile's third act: A push to end industry overage fees
snippet.description: The "Uncarrier" is out with a campaign to get its competitors to eliminate the fees charged when customers go over their allotted voice minutes, text messages, or data.

snippet.title: T-Mobile's next act: Attracting tablet buyers with free data
snippet.description: The company will let new and existing postpaid customers add an LTE slate to their existing plans and get nearly 1.2GB of free data through the end of the year.

snippet.title: For Pleo the robot dinosaur, a second act in an American life
snippet.description: In 2007 and 2008, the cute and cuddly Pleo was a huge hit. Then its maker went out of business, and the dinosaur disappeared from view. So what is it doing at CES 2014?

snippet.title: Congressional leaders call for Communications Act makeover
snippet.description: Reps. Fred Upton (R-Mich) and Greg Walden (R-Ore.) say it's time to bring the 1996 law, which governs the nation's communications networks, into the 21st century.

snippet.title: In letter to German lawmakers, Snowden speaks of his 'moral duty to act'
snippet.description: In note delivered to German legislators, former NSA contractor defends his leak of documents and says he'd be willing to travel to Germany to testify in probe of US spying there.

snippet.title: SOPA foes warn: Not much time left to act
snippet.description: If you want to head off looming votes on the Stop Online Piracy Act and the Senate's Protect IP Act, act now, congressional foes of the proposals say.

snippet.title: Five ways to train the Philips Hue to act automagically
snippet.description: That new car smell wore off, and now you're left wondering if the Hue is just a glorified light bulb. Sulk no more -- here are five ways to get more out of your smart light bulbs.
